// Reserved-keyword regression: `send` is the actor message-send keyword
// (`actor ! Message { ... }`), so a top-level `send() -> int { ... }`
// must error rather than silently producing a binary that drops the
// function and crashes at runtime.
//
// Before the fix, the parser advanced past TOKEN_SEND in the top-level
// dispatch's default case, the function body got reparsed as
// statements (mostly fine), and the named definition was lost — call
// sites compiled to `rc;` (variable-as-statement) instead of
// `rc = send();`. The user got a successful build with a binary that
// referenced an undefined symbol.

send() -> int { return 0 }

main() {
    rc = send()
    println(rc)
}
